How To Perform the Uwaysi / Uways Al-Qarani (Veysel Karane) Dhikr Preparation: 1-   Get into a silent, peaceful mood before start performing the Dhikr (not loudly, as much as you could hear your own voice).    2-   Better to be alone ideally (when possible).     3-   You have to be in a well-mannered and polite mood, without forgetting in whose presence you are before.  4-    You should have performed your ablution (wudu) earlier. 5-     There is no spesific time period to perform the dhikr, you can start your dhikr whenever you feel most ready to make it and feel most available within the day.  6-     However, ideally the best times to make the Uwaysi dhikr are either before and after the Morning Salat, and before you go to sleep at nights. Dhikr must be performed twice a day: first in the light of the morning, this means you can make it at any time during the day, and then secondly at the darkness of the night and so that means in the evening or night times. Allah says: â€œWhile everyone is in sleep; my servant mentioned Me as well as my Messenger in the absence of the othersâ€ thus Allah will love the Dhikr performer a lot.  Performing the Dhikr:  1-  Before you start doing your dikhr, initially recite Basmala : â€œB-ismi-llahi r-rahmani r-rahimâ€ and then you must first say: ''Tawba Astaghfirullah'' for 100 times repeatedly (alternatively you can say â€˜Astaghfirullah El Azimâ€™ too).       2-      Then without saying any â€˜Basmalaâ€™, we send Salawats to our beloved Prophet Muhammad (pbuh) at least for 100 times. So you will say; â€œAllahumme Salli Ala Seyyidina Muhammedâ€, or another salawat of your choice, at least for 100 times or more than 100 repeatedly. There is no limit in the numbers of Salawats. If you would ask us, we would advice to say it minimum for 100 times. However for those who would like to make it, we can also advice for 132 though this is not essential. If you would ask why 132, please then refer to our book, Love of Uwaysi-1. 3-      Once you finish saying Salawats, you must then read -11- Surah Al-Ikhlas and -1- Surah Al-Fatihah only, these numbers are precise.   4-   Gift Section: And then send the Salawats and Surahs that you read as a gift to: â€œMy glorious Allah, I would like to give the rewards of the Surahs and Salawats that I have read to; our beloved Prophet Mohammadâ€™s (pbuh) mubarak soul, his Ahl al-Bayt, his friends and companions, his high family, to all righteous servants, to Al-Khidr (as) and the derwishes (saints) that he loves, to the helping sultans, and to hodjas (teachers) teaching us and to their hodjas, and to all Uwaysis, as a gift. Amen. Note that, you can also include your own relatives, friends, actually anyone that you love at the final part of the gift.   5-      Tawhid: Finally, Say Auzu Basmala for once (A'uzu billahi minashaitanir rajim Bismillahi rahmani Rahim), and then you must recite Tawhid, so say; â€œLa Ilahe Illallahâ€repeatedly at least minimum for 100 times, or more.   **Please also note that, 11 Ikhlas and 1 Fatihah shall not be read once after completing the dhikr.** Please visit our website www.veyselkarane.com for further information. May Allah's, His Messengers, His beloved ones greetings and blessings be upon you.  How To Perform the Uwaysi / Uways Al-Qarani (Veysel Karane) Dhikr Preparation: 1-   Get into a silent, peaceful mood before start performing the Dhikr (not loudly, as much as you could hear your own voice).    2-   Better to be alone ideally (when possible).     3-   You have to be in a well-mannered and polite mood, without forgetting in whose presence you are before.  4-    You should have performed your ablution (wudu) earlier. 5-     There is no spesific time period to perform the dhikr, you can start your dhikr whenever you feel most ready to make it and feel most available within the day.  6-     However, ideally the best times to make the Uwaysi dhikr are either before and after the Morning Salat, and before you go to sleep at nights. Dhikr must be performed twice a day: first in the light of the morning, this means you can make it at any time during the day, and then secondly at the darkness of the night and so that means in the evening or night times. Allah says: â€œWhile everyone is in sleep; my servant mentioned Me as well as my Messenger in the absence of the othersâ€ thus Allah will love the Dhikr performer a lot.  Performing the Dhikr:  1-  Before you start doing your dikhr, initially recite Basmala : â€œB-ismi-llahi r-rahmani r-rahimâ€ and then you must first say: ''Tawba Astaghfirullah'' for 100 times repeatedly (alternatively you can say â€˜Astaghfirullah El Azimâ€™ too).       2-      Then without saying any â€˜Basmalaâ€™, we send Salawats to our beloved Prophet Muhammad (pbuh) at least for 100 times. So you will say; â€œAllahumme Salli Ala Seyyidina Muhammedâ€, or another salawat of your choice, at least for 100 times or more than 100 repeatedly. There is no limit in the numbers of Salawats. If you would ask us, we would advice to say it minimum for 100 times. However for those who would like to make it, we can also advice for 132 though this is not essential. If you would ask why 132, please then refer to our book, Love of Uwaysi-1. 3-      Once you finish saying Salawats, you must then read -11- Surah Al-Ikhlas and -1- Surah Al-Fatihah only, these numbers are precise.   4-   Gift Section: And then send the Salawats and Surahs that you read as a gift to: â€œMy glorious Allah, I would like to give the rewards of the Surahs and Salawats that I have read to; our beloved Prophet Mohammadâ€™s (pbuh) mubarak soul, his Ahl al-Bayt, his friends and companions, his high family, to all righteous servants, to Al-Khidr (as) and the derwishes (saints) that he loves, to the helping sultans, and to hodjas (teachers) teaching us and to their hodjas, and to all Uwaysis, as a gift. Amen. Note that, you can also include your own relatives, friends, actually anyone that you love at the final part of the gift.   5-      Tawhid: Finally, Say Auzu Basmala for once (A'uzu billahi minashaitanir rajim Bismillahi rahmani Rahim), and then you must recite Tawhid, so say; â€œLa Ilahe Illallahâ€repeatedly at least minimum for 100 times, or more.   **Please also note that, 11 Ikhlas and 1 Fatihah shall not be read once after completing the dhikr.** Please visit our website www.veyselkarane.com for further information.
